\date{2024-04-21}
\title{reflexive pair}
\taxon{Definition}
\author{trebor}
\import{common}

\p{
  A \strong{reflexive pair} is the categorical translation of a reflexive relation. It is defined as a pair of arrows #{\partial_0, \partial_1 : X \rightrightarrows Y} with a common section #{r : Y \to X}, i.e. an arrow #{r} such that #{\partial_0 \compose r = \partial_1 \compose r = \id_Y}. A coequalizer of a reflexive pair is called a \strong{reflexive coequalizer}.
}
